The Dublin Gate Theatre was founded by Hilton Edwards (1903-1982) and Miche치l MacLiamm칩ir (1899-1978), two Englishmen who had met touring in Ireland with Anew McMaster's acting company.  The press cuttings books nos. 1, 3-10, 12-66, are those of the Gate and numbered as held by them. Books 2 and 11 are missing. The inclusive dates are 2/10/1928 to 6/2/1971. Much valuable information can be gleaned from the fragile clippings.
